Source: Twitter: AT & # 45; & # 45; & quot; & quot; & quot; & quot; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45
”随着新型冠状病毒肺炎确诊病例激增至欧洲第三（仅次于意法），与意大利隔海相望的西班牙宣布提升防控措施，“尽一切所需”避免该国成为第二个意大利。
With the number of confirmed cases of new coronavirus pneumonia soaring to Europe's third highest (after Italy), Spain, across the sea from Italy, has announced that it has stepped up control measures to "do what is necessary" to prevent the country from becoming a second Italy.
从3月11日起，重灾区马德里大区、东北部巴斯克自治区、北部葡萄酒产区拉里奥哈将关闭所有学校、托儿所和老年人日托中心。
From 11 March, all schools, nurseries and day-care centres for the elderly will be closed in the regions of Madrid, Basque Country in the north-east and La Rioja in the northern wine-producing region.
西班牙国会第三大党、极右翼党派Vox的秘书长史密斯（Javier Ortega Smith）被确诊感染新冠病毒，而他周日还参加了该党组织的大型集会。
Javier Ortega Smith, secretary-general of the far-right Vox, Spain's third-largest party, was diagnosed with the new crown virus, and attended a major rally organized by the party on Sunday.
据The Local西班牙频道和路透社报道，马德里、巴斯克和拉里奥哈的学校关闭将持续两周。
According to The Local Spanish channel and Reuters, schools in Madrid, Basque and La Rioja will be closed for two weeks.
马德里、拉里奥哈和巴斯克北部两个地区将禁止超过1000人的室内集会。
Indoor gatherings of more than 1,000 people will be banned in Madrid, La Rioja and northern Basque Country.
马德里市政府宣布关闭所有体育中心和图书馆。
The Municipality of Madrid announced the closure of all sports centres and libraries.
与此同时，议会下议院将关闭一周，西班牙足球甲级联赛所有比赛将在没有观众的情况下闭门举行。
Meanwhile, the lower house of parliament will be closed for a week and all Spanish Serie A tournaments will be held behind closed doors without spectators.
政府还提倡全国的银行和公司员工在家办公。
The government also promotes home-based work for banks and company employees across the country.
截至10日晚上7点，西班牙累计确诊病例上升到1695例，其中死亡36例，另有至少100人病情危重。
By 7 p.m. Thursday, the cumulative number of confirmed cases in Spain had risen to 1,695, with 36 deaths and at least 100 people in critical condition.
而周日，累计确诊病例仅589例，短短两天内，确诊病例上升近三倍。
The cumulative number of confirmed cases on Sunday was only 589, a nearly threefold increase in the number of confirmed cases in just two days.
在死亡病例中有至少30人为69岁以上的老年人，大部分住在养老院。
At least 30 of the deaths occurred among persons over the age of 69, most of whom were living in nursing homes.
至此，西班牙成为欧洲确诊病例数量第三的国家，仅次于意大利和法国。
As a result, Spain has the third highest number of confirmed cases in Europe, after Italy and France.
其中，马德里大区的确诊病例达到782例，占西班牙总确诊病例的近一半。
Of these, 782 cases were diagnosed in the Madrid region, accounting for nearly half of all confirmed cases in Spain.
马德里大区政府已下令每日对公共交通进行消毒。
Madrid's regional government has ordered daily disinfection of public transport.
图片来源：The Local周二，国会第三大党、极右翼党派Vox确认，该党秘书长史密斯确诊感染新冠病毒。
Source: The Local confirmed Tuesday that the party's third-largest party, the far-right party Vox, confirmed the party's secretary-general was diagnosed with the new crown virus.
而周日，Vox在马德里举行了大型集会，史密斯还发表了讲话。
On Sunday, Vox held a big rally in Madrid, and Smith spoke.
Vox已经对周日的集会表示道歉，同时呼吁政府采取边境管控等更严厉的防控措施。
Vox has apologized for Sunday's rally and called for tougher controls, including border controls.
除了Vox的集会，周日马德里多地还举行了国际妇女节大游行活动。
In addition to the Vox rally, there was an International Women's Day parade in Madrid on Sunday.
据马德里大区政府估算，当天共有67场示威活动和游行。
Madrid's regional government estimated that there were 67 demonstrations and marches that day.
眼见确诊病例攀升，西班牙政府于本周开始采取大动作。
The Spanish government began a major campaign this week to see the number of confirmed cases climb.
周一，中央政府与各地方政府达成一致，采取关闭学校等措施加大防控，防止疫情蔓延。
On Monday, the central government and local governments agreed to close schools and other measures to step up control and prevent the disease from spreading.
西班牙卫生部长伊拉（Salvador Illa）周二表示，西班牙将避免“意大利的情况重现”，“我们相信通过目前采取的措施，我们能避免。
Spanish Health Minister Salvador Illa said Tuesday that Spain would avoid "a repeat of the situation in Italy" and that "we believe that with the measures we are taking we can avoid it."
如果需要采取其他措施，我们会采取行动”。
If other measures are needed, we will take action. "
截至10日下午6点，意大利累计确诊病例10149例，其中死亡631例，与一天前相比增加了168例死亡病例。
As of 6 p.m. on the 10th, Italy had 10,149 confirmed cases, of which 631 were deaths, an increase of 168 deaths compared to the previous day.
按此计算，意大利新冠肺炎病亡率已达到6.2%。
According to this calculation, the Italian crown pneumonia mortality rate has reached 6.2%.
西班牙已经暂停与意大利之间的航班直至3月25日。
Spain has suspended flights with Italy until March 25.
意大利和西班牙球员工会则联合发布公告，向欧足联提出暂停两国球队间欧战的申请。
The Italian and Spanish players' unions issued a joint communique to UEFA requesting a suspension of the European war between the two teams.
西班牙首相桑切斯则表示，政府将“尽一切所需，在所需的地点和时间采取措施”，以挺过此次危机。
Spanish Prime Minister Jose Antonio Sánchez said the government would do "everything it needs, where and when it is needed" to survive the crisis.
本周四，政府还将推出一系列经济扶持计划，以帮助中小企业和因学校关闭而需在家看护子女的父母。
On Thursday, the government will also launch a series of economic support programs to help small and medium-sized businesses and parents who have to stay at home to look after their children as schools close.
虽然与意大利相比，西班牙的经济更为强劲，但疫情势必让该国所依赖的旅游业遭受打击。
Although Spain's economy is stronger than Italy's, the epidemic is bound to hit the tourism industry, on which the country depends.
旅游业占西班牙GDP的15%，提供280万个工作岗位。
Tourism accounts for 15 per cent of Spain's GDP and provides 2.8 million jobs.
每年3月在瓦伦西亚举行的法雅节庆典已经推迟，西班牙卫生部呼吁全国民众避免非必要的出行。
Faya celebrations in Valencia are postponed each March, and Spain's health ministry is calling on the nation to avoid unnecessary travel.
为应对今后政府可能采取封城等升级措施，马德里多家超市已经出现抢购。
Several Madrid supermarkets have snapped up bids in anticipation of a possible government move to block the city.
一名顾客在接受《金融时报》采访时称大家现在开始害怕了，“政府之前表现太被动了，应该早点采取措施，现在问题已经更突出了”。
In an interview with the Financial Times, one customer said people were now starting to fear, saying "the government has been too passive before and should have taken action earlier, and now the problem is more acute."
超市排队。
Supermarket queues.
